    <body>
      <section eId="sec_182">
        <num>182</num>
        <heading>Diversion of funds dedicated to public transportation systems to the general fund of the state or to any other purpose, is prohibited</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_182__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The amount of the diversion from dedicated mass transit funds;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_182__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The amount diverted from each fund;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_182__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The amount diverted expressed as current monthly transit fares;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_182__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The cumulative amount of diversion from dedicated mass transit\nfunds during the preceding five years;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_182__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The date or dates when the diversion is to occur; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_182__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A detailed estimate of the impact of diversion from dedicated mass\ntransit funds will have on the level of public transportation system\nservice, maintenance, security, and the current capital program.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
